  lines:
  - I walk out of the bakery into an alleyway after getting some lunch and coffee.
  - 'A strange feeling pulled me towards it. '
  - I check my surroundings, making sure no one is watching me as I enter the alley.
  - The further I walk the further it seems to stretch
  - 'A chill runs up my spine. I turn but nothing is there. '
  - "I could\u2019ve sworn it felt like someone or something was watching m-"
